SIMPLE: gloze
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gloze
<hw>Gloze</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Glozed</conjf><pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Glozing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>glosen</ets>, F.
<ets>gloser</ets>. See <er>gloss</er> explanation.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To flatter; to wheedle; to fawn; to talk
smoothly.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A false, <qex>glozing</qex> parasite.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>glozed</qex> the tempter, and his proem tuned.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give a specious or false meaning; to
ministerpret.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gloze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gloze
<hw>Gloze</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To smooth over; to
palliate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By <qex>glozing</qex> the evil that is in the world.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gloze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Gloze
<hw>Gloze</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Flattery; adulation;
smooth speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now to plain dealing; lay these <qex>glozes</qex> by.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specious show; gloss.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glozer</ent>⟦br⟧
